%h1(id="launching_config" style="margin-top:0")
.section-grouping
  %h2 3. Launching Instances with a Runtime Configuration

  %p
    This section requires the instance to be running (as opposed to stopped). Check this before proceeding.

  %ol
    %li
    Click on the 
    %bMonitor tab and then select
    &rArr; <b>Tabled view</b>. This will display all your information in a format based more suitably for these instructions.
    %li
    Click on the pool you're currently operating within.
    %li
    Within that, click on the name of the deployment. You will now be in the deployment able to edit.
    %li
    Check that the instance is running, and click on the instance.
    %li
    This is where you are able to edit the properities and configuration of the deployable. Select the button, 'Config Parameters' next to the 'Properties' button.
    %li
    Within this, you have the ability to type the desired configuration values in its parameter fields.

  %p
